The article discusses the 25th anniversary of the handover of Hong Kong to China and highlights the erosion of democratic institutions, press freedoms, and civil society groups in Hong Kong. It mentions the aggressive implementation of the National Security Law, which has suppressed political opposition and dissent, leading to the imprisonment or exile of pro-democracy politicians. The article also states that these actions have undermined fundamental freedoms and the rules-based order that maintains global stability. It calls on China to uphold its international obligations and respect the protected rights and freedoms of the people in Hong Kong as outlined in the Basic Law.